arXiv:2408.16576v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: In the late eighties, Hildebrand and Tenenbaum proved an asymptotic formula for the number of positive integers below $x$, having exactly $
u$ distinct prime divisors: $\pi_{
u}(x) \sim x \delta_{
u}(x)$. Here we consider the restricted count $\pi_{
u}(x,y)$ for integers lying in the short interval $[x,x+y]$. Extending the result of Hildebrand-Tenenbaum to this setting, we show that for any $\varepsilon >0$ \[ \pi_{
u}(x,y) \sim y \delta_{
u}(x), \] uniformly over all $1 \le 
u \le \log x/(\log \log x)^{4+\varepsilon}$ and all $x^{7/12 +\varepsilon} \le y \le x$. Consequently, we obtain mean upper bounds for the $k$-fold divisor function $	au_k$ in short intervals, with strong uniformity in $k$.
